Feature: Current Weather API # features/weather.feature:1

  Feature: Current Weather API  # features/weather.feature:1

  @smoke
  Scenario: Get current weather for valid coordinates                               # features/weather.feature:7
    Given the weather API is available                                              # features/steps/weather_steps.py:6
    When I request the current weather for latitude 20.6767 and longitude -103.3475 # features/steps/weather_steps.py:24
    Then the response status code should be 200                                     # features/steps/weather_steps.py:35
    And the response should contain weather data                                    # features/steps/weather_steps.py:43

  @regression
  Scenario: Validate mandatory fields in the response                               # features/weather.feature:13
    Given the weather API is available                                              # features/steps/weather_steps.py:6
    When I request the current weather for latitude 20.6767 and longitude -103.3475 # features/steps/weather_steps.py:24
    Then the response should include "temperature" and "windspeed"                  # features/steps/weather_steps.py:53
    And these fields should contain numeric values                                  # features/steps/weather_steps.py:62

  @regression
  Scenario: Request weather with invalid coordinates                                  # features/weather.feature:19
    Given the weather API is available                                                # features/steps/weather_steps.py:6
    When I request the current weather for latitude 999 and longitude 999             # features/steps/weather_steps.py:24
    Then the response status code should be 400                                       # features/steps/weather_steps.py:35
    And the response body should contain an "Latitude must be in range" error message # features/steps/weather_steps.py:77

